The term '''disease causative agent''' usually refers to the biological [[pathogen]] that causes a disease, such as a [[virus]], [[parasite]], [[fungus]], or [[bacterium]]. Technically, the term can also refer to a [[toxin]] or [[Toxicity|toxic]] chemical that causes illness.

